I mean.

13
00:02:06.430 --> 00:02:07.736
you turned it around.

14
00:02:09.607 --> 00:02:11.131
made a life for yourself.

15
00:02:16.223 --> 00:02:18.355
I guess I just wanted to know

16
00:02:21.750 --> 00:02:23.186
how you did that?

17
00:02:29.105 --> 00:02:32.326
You hear these rare stories. you know?

18
00:02:32.500 --> 00:02:34.066
Of how the impossible happened.

19
00:02:37.461 --> 00:02:38.288
Well.

20
00:02:40.203 --> 00:02:42.510
this is one of those stories.

21
00:03:13.932 --> 00:03:16.848
Hey!

22
00:03:50.534 --> 00:03:54.277
It was the 1950s. but if
you pulled up to our yard.

23
00:03:54.451 --> 00:03:57.019
you would've thought it was the 1850s.

24
00:03:57.193 --> 00:03:59.413
That's how poor we were.

25
00:03:59.587 --> 00:04:02.198
Dad spent most of his time
workin' in the oil fields.

26
00:04:02.372 --> 00:04:04.069
I wish you didn't always have to go.

27
00:04:04.244 --> 00:04:06.594
Hell. that's life. Phil.

28
00:04:06.768 --> 00:04:08.030
It's time you grew up.

29
00:04:12.034 --> 00:04:13.601
Take care of things around here.

30
00:04:15.559 --> 00:04:16.168
You got it?

31
00:04:16.343 --> 00:04:17.213
Yes. sir.

32
00:04:24.568 --> 00:04:25.395
Who's a man?

33
00:04:27.658 --> 00:04:29.094
I'm a man.

34
00:04:29.269 --> 00:04:31.358
Mama provided a different
set of challenges.

35
00:04:33.447 --> 00:04:35.362
- When she had one of her spells.
- Mom. stop it!

36
00:04:35.536 --> 00:04:36.276
- Get outta here!
- You'll go back

37
00:04:36.450 --> 00:04:37.059
to the hospital again!

38
00:04:37.233 --> 00:04:38.626
Get out!

39
00:04:38.800 --> 00:04:39.844
All we could really
do is get outta the way.

40
00:04:40.018 --> 00:04:40.802
No one's takin' me to the hospital.

41
00:04:40.976 --> 00:04:42.151
You gotta calm down!

42
00:04:42.325 --> 00:04:43.761
Please!

43
00:04:43.935 --> 00:04:45.067
Get outta here!

44
00:04:45.241 --> 00:04:46.111
Go!

45
00:04:48.375 --> 00:04:51.203
I started at a
young age. a very young age.

46
00:04:53.336 --> 00:04:55.120
Come to the woods and bringin'
back somethin' you could eat.

47
00:04:57.079 --> 00:05:00.604
Squirrel. ducks. quail.
doves. whatever was there.

48
00:05:01.953 --> 00:05:03.215
The woods became my home.

49
00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:07.263
Sometimes I would just
sit there for hours.

50
00:05:07.437 --> 00:05:08.525
listen to the woods.

51
00:05:09.570 --> 00:05:13.182
They would talk and I
would try and talk back.

52
00:05:17.752 --> 00:05:19.057
I could get lost in them.

53
00:05:20.755 --> 00:05:22.278
They were my refuge.

54
00:05:25.368 --> 00:05:30.373
But sooner or later. the real
world always comes knockin'.

55
00:06:16.941 --> 00:06:18.552
No. no!

56
00:06:18.726 --> 00:06:20.292
No. no!
- Phil!

57
00:06:20.467 --> 00:06:21.642
They're takin' her away again!
- You can't make me!

58
00:06:21.816 --> 00:06:24.035
You can't make me. you can't!

59
00:06:24.209 --> 00:06:25.385
No!

60
00:06:25.559 --> 00:06:26.473
Phil!

61
00:06:26.647 --> 00:06:27.561
Phil. don't let 'em take me!

62
00:06:27.735 --> 00:06:29.171
She ain't done nothin' wrong!

63
00:06:29.345 --> 00:06:31.695
Judy. Judy [screams]!

64
00:06:31.869 --> 00:06:33.305
Phil. Phil. Phil!

65
00:06:35.438 --> 00:06:38.528
Mom [sobs]!

66
00:06:38.702 --> 00:06:39.486
Phil!

67
00:06:39.660 --> 00:06:41.662
Phil. Phil [sobs]!

68
00:07:01.899 --> 00:07:04.772
She was gone for months at a time.

69
00:07:04.946 --> 00:07:06.295
Mama?

70
00:07:06.469 --> 00:07:07.992
While they tried the
only medicine they had.

71
00:07:09.951 --> 00:07:11.126
shock treatment.

72
00:07:12.344 --> 00:07:13.345
Mama?

73
00:07:24.966 --> 00:07:25.923
Why does she keep doin' this stuff

74
00:07:26.097 --> 00:07:27.447
if she knows they'll lock her up?

75
00:07:28.839 --> 00:07:30.319
She can't help it.

76
00:07:30.493 --> 00:07:31.886
It's in her blood or somethin'.

77
00:07:33.061 --> 00:07:34.454
We got that blood in us?

78
00:07:36.499 --> 00:07:38.109
Don't know.

79
00:07:38.283 --> 00:07:40.024
but we'll always look out
for each other. won't we?

80
00:07:40.938 --> 00:07:42.244
You mean that. Phil?

81
00:07:44.246 --> 00:07:45.334
Of course I do. Jan.

82
00:07:47.118 --> 00:07:48.816
Si. go get some taters
from under the house.

83
00:07:48.990 --> 00:07:50.078
Nah. nah. nah.

84
00:07:50.252 --> 00:07:52.384
Hey. last time that possum ran after me.

85
00:07:52.559 --> 00:07:54.996
his teeth were like this big.

86
00:08:00.828 --> 00:08:01.872
I didn't know it at the time.

87
00:08:02.046 --> 00:08:04.614
but just up the road a few miles lived

88
00:08:04.788 --> 00:08:05.963
a girl who would soon become

89
00:08:06.137 --> 00:08:08.836
the most important person in my life.

90
00:08:11.316 --> 00:08:12.448
Kay Carroway.

91
00:08:13.797 --> 00:08:14.798
Oh. damn it!

92
00:08:14.972 --> 00:08:16.408
Language. Mom!

93
00:08:16.583 --> 00:08:17.845
Kay. pick up your toys.
they nearly killed me.

94
00:08:18.019 --> 00:08:19.673
and then you go get those over there.

95
00:08:19.847 --> 00:08:21.283
- Compared to us.
- Stay on your feet.

96
00:08:21.457 --> 00:08:22.806
- Kay was rich.
- gonna be stockin'

97
00:08:22.980 --> 00:08:23.590
the store tonight. and I
can't do it without you.

98
00:08:23.764 --> 00:08:24.852
Oh-

99
00:08:25.026 --> 00:08:26.027
They owned the general store in town.

100
00:08:26.201 --> 00:08:28.508
so we equated that with filthy rich.

101
00:08:28.682 --> 00:08:31.554
Y'all could close stores on
Sundays and come to church.

102
00:08:31.728 --> 00:08:33.600
It'd be good for your soul. Daddy.

103
00:08:33.774 --> 00:08:36.080
Sunday's our best day. Katie-bug.

104
00:08:37.517 --> 00:08:38.822
You may say a prayer for us.

105
00:08:38.996 --> 00:08:40.607
especially about sellin'
them three roasts today

106
00:08:40.781 --> 00:08:43.305
before I have to throw 'em
out and lose money on 'em.

107
00:08:44.175 --> 00:08:45.046
Hey?

108
00:08:46.308 --> 00:08:47.483
Don't you get caught readin'

109
00:08:47.657 --> 00:08:50.051
them pioneer books in church again.

110
00:08:52.009 --> 00:08:53.837
Just in case.

111
00:08:54.011 --> 00:08:55.447
"Little House on the
Prairie." new edition.

112
00:08:55.622 --> 00:08:57.145
I don't have this one [laughs].

113
00:08:57.319 --> 00:08:58.102
I know [chuckles].

114
00:08:58.276 --> 00:08:59.234
Says there's all kinds

115
00:08:59.408 --> 00:09:00.844
of new maps and drawings in there.

116
00:09:01.018 --> 00:09:01.976
Thanks. Daddy.

117
00:09:05.675 --> 00:09:08.069
Kay wasn't like the other kids.

118
00:09:08.243 --> 00:09:09.418
They judged us.

119
00:09:10.288 --> 00:09:11.463
She didn't.

120
00:09:20.734 --> 00:09:23.171
I guess she saw somethin' else.

121
00:09:25.390 --> 00:09:28.306
Look like the riff-raff's
blowing in from the field.

122
00:09:28.480 --> 00:09:30.482
Y'all should be ashamed of yourselves.

123
00:09:31.483 --> 00:09:34.138
Wowie. look at this.

124
00:09:34.312 --> 00:09:35.575
What are these called?

125
00:09:35.749 --> 00:09:36.706
Hubcaps.

126
00:09:36.880 --> 00:09:38.360
Dang!

127
00:09:38.534 --> 00:09:40.275
Pa's truck ain't never had these.

128
00:09:41.842 --> 00:09:44.018
Must be a load of
millionaires here in town.

129
00:09:47.978 --> 00:09:49.066
Turns out there was somethin'

130
00:09:49.240 --> 00:09:51.155
besides huntin' I was actually good at.

131
00:09:52.330 --> 00:09:53.288
I was born with it.

132
00:09:54.942 --> 00:09:57.597
That's how I became the
high school quarterback.

133
00:10:04.691 --> 00:10:06.736
Down. set. hut!

134
00:10:23.666 --> 00:10:24.711
Hey. way to play fellas.

135
00:10:24.885 --> 00:10:25.842
You gotta stop runnin' like that.

136
00:10:26.016 --> 00:10:27.627
You put me out of a job.

137
00:10:27.801 --> 00:10:28.715
Pretty sure you gotta get on the field

138
00:10:28.889 --> 00:10:31.456
before you can lose that job. son.

139
00:10:31.631 --> 00:10:33.458
Talk about your pioneer man. Kay.

140
00:10:34.285 --> 00:10:35.983
Maybe he'll walk you off
the field after the game.

141
00:10:36.157 --> 00:10:37.593
Phil Robertson. the quarterback?

142
00:10:37.767 --> 00:10:39.247
You gotta be kiddin' me.

143
00:10:39.421 --> 00:10:41.031
I seen the way he looks at you.

144
00:10:41.205 --> 00:10:42.642
Hey. Phil
Robertson. can I get a statement?

145
00:10:43.730 --> 00:10:44.861
Nah. nah.

146
00:10:45.035 --> 00:10:46.471
You wanna talk to Si Robertson right here.

147
00:10:46.646 --> 00:10:47.821
Real hero of the game.

148
00:10:47.995 --> 00:10:48.909
Si Robertson?

149
00:10:49.083 --> 00:10:50.562
Did you even play?

150
00:10:50.737 --> 00:10:52.303
Boy. did I even play?

151
00:10:52.477 --> 00:10:54.044
I was so fast like lightning.

152
00:10:54.218 --> 00:10:55.306
that's why it probably didn't even feel

153
00:10:55.480 --> 00:10:57.004
like you saw me out there on that field.

154
00:10:57.178 --> 00:10:59.006
Miss Kay Carroway.

155
00:10:59.180 --> 00:11:00.094
Hey. Phil.

156
00:11:00.268 --> 00:11:01.182
Hey.

157
00:11:02.313 --> 00:11:03.924
Look. I know we don't know
each other all that well.

158
00:11:04.098 --> 00:11:07.449
but think maybe I could walk
you off the field tonight?

159
00:11:07.623 --> 00:11:08.319
I'd like that.

160
00:11:09.712 --> 00:11:10.713
Okay.

161
00:11:10.887 --> 00:11:12.323
So we walked off the field together

162
00:11:12.497 --> 00:11:14.021
and she offered me a ride home.

163
00:11:14.891 --> 00:11:16.458
I didn't even have the luxury of goin'

164
00:11:16.632 --> 00:11:18.721
on my first date without
at least one third wheel.

165
00:11:18.895 --> 00:11:20.288
And that's when I went down to pet

166
00:11:20.462 --> 00:11:22.812
what I thought was a
dog. and no way. okay?

167
00:11:22.986 --> 00:11:25.119
Turned out it was a five-pound squirrel.

168
00:11:25.293 --> 00:11:26.686
Sorry about this.

169
00:11:26.860 --> 00:11:28.818
I mean. I really do despise beavers.

170
00:11:28.992 --> 00:11:32.039
but I also respect their
work ethic and determination.

171
00:11:36.565 --> 00:11:37.871
You're gonna stay in the car.

172
00:11:38.045 --> 00:11:39.916
- What do you mean?
- This is my date.

173
00:11:40.090 --> 00:11:41.178
so you're stayin'.

174
00:11:41.352 --> 00:11:43.050
I'll be skin and bone if I don't eat.

175
00:11:43.224 --> 00:11:44.138
I hate to break it to ya.
honey. but you already are.

176
00:11:44.312 --> 00:11:46.227
Hey Jack. I am wastin' away.

177
00:11:46.401 --> 00:11:47.358
All right. fine. fine.

178
00:11:47.532 --> 00:11:48.882
Quit your yappin'.

179
00:11:49.056 --> 00:11:49.578
I'll get you somethin'.
but you're stayin' here.

180
00:11:49.752 --> 00:11:50.622
All right.

181
00:11:54.235 --> 00:11:55.062
All right.

182
00:11:58.195 --> 00:11:59.675
Sorry about that.

183
00:11:59.849 --> 00:12:01.546
♪ Yeah. yeah. yeah. yeah ♪

184
00:12:12.601 --> 00:12:13.950
I know girls are supposed to act

185
00:12:14.124 --> 00:12:15.038
like they don't eat
nothin' on these dates.

186
00:12:15.212 --> 00:12:17.649
but I am absolutely starvin'.

187
00:12:17.824 --> 00:12:18.520
Hey. Rachel?

188
00:12:18.694 --> 00:12:20.217
Hey. Kay.

189
00:12:20.391 --> 00:12:22.089
Could I get two muffy
sandwiches and a large fry?

190
00:12:22.263 --> 00:12:23.133
What you want? I can pay.

191
00:12:23.307 --> 00:12:24.091
Hey. no. come on.

192
00:12:24.265 --> 00:12:26.397
You drove. I got this.

193
00:12:29.661 --> 00:12:31.751
Uh. you know. I don't really
eat after the games anyway.

194
00:12:31.925 --> 00:12:34.405
so I think I'm just gonna
get something for Si. so.

195
00:12:35.755 --> 00:12:36.451
You know what?

196
00:12:36.625 --> 00:12:38.409
I changed my mind.

197
00:12:38.583 --> 00:12:39.976
Could you just gimme one of
those single grilled cheeses.

198
00:12:40.150 --> 00:12:42.196
and Rachel. you owe me
a fry from last week.

199
00:12:42.370 --> 00:12:43.675
so don't go cheatin' out on me again.

200
00:12:43.850 --> 00:12:45.460
Okay.

201
00:12:45.634 --> 00:12:47.375
Fries are for skinny bones.

202
00:12:51.074 --> 00:12:52.119
In those days.

203
00:12:52.293 --> 00:12:53.250
it was a nightmare dealin' with Mama.

204
00:12:53.424 --> 00:12:55.078
Where is it?

205
00:12:55.252 --> 00:12:57.820
When she was good. she was
great. Funny. sharp. kind.

206
00:12:57.994 --> 00:12:59.300
Ma. what are you lookin' for?

207
00:12:59.474 --> 00:13:00.780
The money.

208
00:13:00.954 --> 00:13:02.390
Where's the money?

209
00:13:02.564 --> 00:13:03.608
I keep tellin' you.
we ain't got no money.

210
00:13:03.783 --> 00:13:05.828
At least not in the way you're sayin'.

211
00:13:06.002 --> 00:13:07.047
Oh no. from your pa.

212
00:13:07.221 --> 00:13:08.439
He's been sendin' it.

213
00:13:08.613 --> 00:13:10.224
But when it wasn't her day-

214
00:13:10.398 --> 00:13:11.660
I got back
from the hospital and-

215
00:13:11.834 --> 00:13:13.705
Life was hell for all of us.

216
00:13:13.880 --> 00:13:15.577
Yes. Mama. and Pa did send it.

217
00:13:15.751 --> 00:13:16.796
We've been usin' it.

218
00:13:16.970 --> 00:13:18.145
Jan needed actual clothes for school.

219
00:13:18.319 --> 00:13:20.364
Si needed shoes for football.

220
00:13:20.538 --> 00:13:22.758
Everything around us costs money.

221
00:13:26.370 --> 00:13:27.284
Why are you wearing that?

222
00:13:27.458 --> 00:13:28.546
Why are you all dressed up?

223
00:13:30.940 --> 00:13:32.812
'Cause I got a date tonight.

224
00:13:34.291 --> 00:13:36.250
You got a date [laughs]?

225
00:13:36.424 --> 00:13:38.774
Oh. baby. with who. huh?

226
00:13:41.516 --> 00:13:42.778
Kay Carroway.

227
00:13:46.608 --> 00:13:47.565
Carroway?

228
00:13:50.046 --> 00:13:52.135
That rich family in town?

229
00:13:54.964 --> 00:13:56.226
Well. that's nice.

230
00:14:00.187 --> 00:14:03.625
You gonna leave me. Phil [sobbing]?

231
00:14:03.799 --> 00:14:05.235
You gonna leave me. Phil?

232
00:14:05.409 --> 00:14:06.715
Is that what you're gonna do?

233
00:14:06.889 --> 00:14:07.542
- I'm not leave-
- You gonna leave me?

234
00:14:07.716 --> 00:14:09.196
I'm not leavin'!

235
00:14:13.200 --> 00:14:14.941
Don't go.

236
00:14:15.115 --> 00:14:16.116
Don't go.

237
00:14:16.290 --> 00:14:18.988
Don't go like your father [sobbing].

238
00:14:26.778 --> 00:14:29.259
- Hey.
- Hey. you ready to go?

239
00:14:31.044 --> 00:14:31.871
What's wrong?

240
00:14:33.002 --> 00:14:33.698
Nothin'.

241
00:14:33.873 --> 00:14:35.483
Everything's fine.

242
00:14:35.657 --> 00:14:36.397
No. I can tell you look
like you've seen a ghost.

243
00:14:36.571 --> 00:14:37.441
What...

244
00:14:38.573 --> 00:14:40.662
Oh. my Mama's been
actin' up again is all.

245
00:14:40.836 --> 00:14:42.229
but it's fine. we got our date tonight.

246
00:14:42.403 --> 00:14:43.230
It's...

247
00:14:45.841 --> 00:14:46.973
There's just a lot goin' on.

248
00:14:47.147 --> 00:14:50.019
Hey. whoa. it's okay.

249
00:14:50.193 --> 00:14:51.716
We can figure it out together.

250
00:14:52.804 --> 00:14:53.631
No. no. all right?

251
00:14:53.805 --> 00:14:55.459
You shouldn't...

252
00:14:55.633 --> 00:14:56.939
No. you're not gonna have
to deal with any of this.

253
00:14:57.113 --> 00:14:58.462
Hey. who needs another
muffy at Fertitta's?

254
00:14:58.636 --> 00:14:59.811
I've got an idea.

255
00:15:03.206 --> 00:15:05.034
Thank you again for bringin' all this.

256
00:15:05.208 --> 00:15:06.949
Well. just because my
parents own a grocery store

257
00:15:07.123 --> 00:15:08.820
don't mean I know how
to cook anything in it.

258
00:15:08.995 --> 00:15:11.084
Well. honey. that I can teach.

259
00:15:11.258 --> 00:15:12.607
Always start with some butter here.

260
00:15:12.781 --> 00:15:14.348
baby. okay?

261
00:15:14.522 --> 00:15:15.915
Give us a snack. all right?

262
00:15:16.089 --> 00:15:17.307
No one-
- Coca-Cola?

263
00:15:17.481 --> 00:15:19.440
Dang. she is rich.
- Jan!

264
00:15:19.614 --> 00:15:20.484
Where's the tea?

265
00:15:22.573 --> 00:15:23.792
Hey. grab me somethin'. would ya?

266
00:15:23.966 --> 00:15:25.098
Hey. I hear that.

267
00:15:25.272 --> 00:15:26.926
You steal a bite before it's ready.

