280
00:16:02.309 --> 00:16:05.660
and though she probably won't admit it.

281
00:16:07.314 --> 00:16:09.969
she really misses my pa
when he's on the job.

282
00:16:10.143 --> 00:16:11.622
Yeah. yeah.

283
00:16:11.796 --> 00:16:13.059
You know. she seemed okay.

284
00:16:14.495 --> 00:16:16.888
There's this other
side to her. you know?

285
00:16:17.063 --> 00:16:18.194
And you can't predict it.

286
00:16:18.368 --> 00:16:19.804
It just kinda-

287
00:16:19.979 --> 00:16:21.850
You ain't never have
to be ashamed of that.

288
00:16:24.418 --> 00:16:25.941
Wait. shh. shh.

289
00:16:26.115 --> 00:16:27.160
- What is it?
- Hear that?

290
00:16:28.900 --> 00:16:32.643
That's a pintail.

291
00:16:40.347 --> 00:16:42.044
You love it out here.

292
00:16:43.176 --> 00:16:44.003
I do.

293
00:16:45.700 --> 00:16:47.180
It is beautiful.

294
00:16:54.535 --> 00:16:56.667
We can get a place out here. you and I.

295
00:16:57.668 --> 00:16:58.669
a little shack up on the river

296
00:16:58.843 --> 00:17:00.628
and I could spend my days fishin'.

297
00:17:01.672 --> 00:17:03.065
I...

298
00:17:06.460 --> 00:17:07.243
I'm sorry.

299
00:17:08.723 --> 00:17:10.594
A girl like you definitely
don't wanna spend

300
00:17:10.768 --> 00:17:11.682
her time like that.

301
00:17:13.989 --> 00:17:16.818
My dad used to read me
pioneer stories every night.

302
00:17:16.992 --> 00:17:18.646
What's a pioneer story?

303
00:17:18.820 --> 00:17:20.996
You know. like movin' out
west. livin' off the land.

304
00:17:21.170 --> 00:17:23.259
makin' your own butter. that kinda thing.

305
00:17:24.173 --> 00:17:26.349
There's always a good love story too.

306
00:17:26.523 --> 00:17:27.916
I used to go to bed dreamin'

307
00:17:28.090 --> 00:17:30.136
about how amazin' that
kinda life would be.

308
00:17:30.310 --> 00:17:34.227
So. yeah. a little place by the
river would be just the thing.

309
00:17:36.751 --> 00:17:39.362
You really are the perfect
woman. Miss Kay Carroway.

310
00:17:43.584 --> 00:17:46.065
Kay fell right in with my family.

311
00:17:46.239 --> 00:17:48.719
In my mind. we were a perfect fit.

312
00:17:51.548 --> 00:17:53.942
Phil has been an All-State
quarterback this year.

313
00:17:54.116 --> 00:17:55.204
They've been saying he's gonna

314
00:17:55.378 --> 00:17:56.814
get lots of offers from colleges to play.

315
00:17:56.988 --> 00:18:00.557
Football is such a rough sport to me.

316
00:18:00.731 --> 00:18:02.385
Seems like a waste of time.

317
00:18:02.559 --> 00:18:05.606
I mean. are they gonna pay
you a lot of money to play?

318
00:18:05.780 --> 00:18:07.912
I'm sure they got scholarships and such.

319
00:18:08.087 --> 00:18:09.349
Am I right. Phil?

320
00:18:09.523 --> 00:18:10.698
Oh. yes. Sir.

321
00:18:10.872 --> 00:18:12.003
Yes. Ma'am.

322
00:18:12.178 --> 00:18:14.397
See. there you go. Wanita.

323
00:18:16.486 --> 00:18:18.706
You know. that reminds me.

324
00:18:18.880 --> 00:18:22.188
Kay. guess who came into the store today?

325
00:18:24.233 --> 00:18:25.974
Mrs. Watson.

326
00:18:26.148 --> 00:18:28.933
Now. her boy is nearly
outta medical school.

327
00:18:29.108 --> 00:18:31.022
A doctor. you know?

328
00:18:31.197 --> 00:18:34.678
And I remember. oo. he
used to come around.

329
00:18:34.852 --> 00:18:36.680
He had eyes for you.

330
00:18:39.466 --> 00:18:41.816
Wanita. you look like
you're runnin' empty there.

331
00:18:41.990 --> 00:18:44.558
Well. so is my beer.

332
00:18:45.602 --> 00:18:47.213
I would love another.

333
00:18:47.387 --> 00:18:48.475
Phil. wait!

334
00:18:48.649 --> 00:18:49.650
I'm sorry about my Mama.

335
00:18:49.824 --> 00:18:50.955
Phil!
- You ain't gotta

336
00:18:51.130 --> 00:18:52.479
be polite anymore. Kay.
- Please!

337
00:18:52.653 --> 00:18:54.568
Just. I'm sorry about my Mama. okay?

338
00:18:54.742 --> 00:18:56.265
This not gonna work.

339
00:18:58.137 --> 00:19:00.487
It's huntin' season.
- No.

340
00:19:00.661 --> 00:19:01.792
- I gotta go.
- No [sobs].

341
00:19:09.931 --> 00:19:12.673
So. you just broke up
with her just like that?

342
00:19:13.891 --> 00:19:15.110
It was huntin' season.

343
00:19:19.723 --> 00:19:21.160
- That's a bad move.
- Yep.

344
00:19:22.596 --> 00:19:23.945
One of many.

345
00:19:27.992 --> 00:19:29.298
How'd you get her back then?

346
00:19:29.472 --> 00:19:33.172
Hey!

347
00:19:33.346 --> 00:19:35.348
Now!

348
00:20:13.516 --> 00:20:14.691
Phil!

349
00:20:14.865 --> 00:20:16.127
Phil. it's Kay!

350
00:20:29.140 --> 00:20:31.099
The death of Kay's
father came out of nowhere

351
00:20:31.273 --> 00:20:33.536
and left a big hole in her family.

352
00:20:35.843 --> 00:20:36.713
Kay.

353
00:20:39.194 --> 00:20:40.064
I love you.

354
00:20:41.283 --> 00:20:43.111
I'm sorry for runnin' off like that.

355
00:20:46.549 --> 00:20:47.550
It wasn't long after her daddy died

356
00:20:47.724 --> 00:20:49.726
that her mama spiraled down quickly.

357
00:20:49.900 --> 00:20:52.076
She fought a hard battle with alcohol.

358
00:20:52.251 --> 00:20:54.035
and the alcohol eventually won.

359
00:20:54.949 --> 00:20:56.167
I was all she had.

360
00:20:56.342 --> 00:20:59.083
but in a lot of ways she was all I had.

361
00:20:59.954 --> 00:21:00.781
Wait.

362
00:21:02.043 --> 00:21:02.870
You think it's right that we're doin' this

363
00:21:03.044 --> 00:21:04.480
when we ain't married?

364
00:21:07.875 --> 00:21:12.836
I. Phil Robertson promise to
love and be with you forever.

365
00:21:15.143 --> 00:21:18.755
I. Kay Carroway promise to
love and be with you forever.

366
00:21:20.366 --> 00:21:22.237
♪ Just one kiss from your sweet lips ♪

367
00:21:22.411 --> 00:21:24.413
♪ Will tell me that your love real ♪

368
00:21:24.587 --> 00:21:25.980
So after all that.

369
00:21:26.154 --> 00:21:27.808
because of my skillset
throwin' a football.

370
00:21:27.982 --> 00:21:30.158
I headed off to Louisiana Tech.

371
00:21:31.551 --> 00:21:33.292
Great game. boys!

372
00:21:33.466 --> 00:21:35.250
Kay was only a junior
in high school at the time.

373
00:21:35.424 --> 00:21:37.296
but we had a baby on the way.

374
00:21:38.645 --> 00:21:40.211
and it was pretty rough on Kay.

375
00:21:42.866 --> 00:21:44.825
Tried to balance takin' care of my family

376
00:21:44.999 --> 00:21:49.743
and school and football.
but it was too much.

377
00:21:51.222 --> 00:21:53.181
Eventually I had to quit football.

378
00:21:53.355 --> 00:21:54.965
You ever think about that. man?

379
00:21:55.139 --> 00:21:56.576
You coulda been big.

380
00:21:56.750 --> 00:21:59.709
I'm talkin' like cereal box big.

381
00:21:59.883 --> 00:22:01.102
Wheaties big.

382
00:22:02.146 --> 00:22:04.540
"The" Terry Bradshaw was your number two.

383
00:22:04.714 --> 00:22:06.020
"The" Terry Bradshaw.

384
00:22:07.935 --> 00:22:10.590
I say it worked out pretty good for him.

385
00:22:10.764 --> 00:22:11.808
Yeah. I'd say so.

386
00:22:12.983 --> 00:22:14.289
Hey. you and him get along?

387
00:22:17.248 --> 00:22:19.642
Can I take
this thing off now. Phil?

388
00:22:19.816 --> 00:22:20.730
No.

389
00:22:20.904 --> 00:22:22.036
Can I at least sit up?

390
00:22:22.210 --> 00:22:23.646
I told ya if you wanna come out here.

391
00:22:23.820 --> 00:22:25.169
this is how it's gonna be.

392
00:22:27.171 --> 00:22:28.303
Yeah. I thought you were joking.

393
00:22:28.477 --> 00:22:30.392
I never joke about fishin'.

394
00:22:30.566 --> 00:22:32.699
Can't be givin' away my secret spots.

395
00:22:32.873 --> 00:22:33.874
not even to you.

396
00:22:36.746 --> 00:22:38.226
All right. take it off.

397
00:22:38.400 --> 00:22:39.793
- Yeah?
- Yeah. now.

398
00:22:39.967 --> 00:22:41.142
♪ Saturday night we're goin' fishin' ♪

399
00:22:41.316 --> 00:22:42.622
Woo!

400
00:22:42.796 --> 00:22:44.101
Got my hair all messed
up and everything. man.

401
00:22:44.275 --> 00:22:45.581
You're fine.

402
00:22:45.755 --> 00:22:47.670
Take a look.

403
00:22:47.844 --> 00:22:48.976
♪ Don't forget the frying pan
and bring along some manners ♪

404
00:22:49.150 --> 00:22:50.325
Sorta special.

405
00:22:50.499 --> 00:22:52.196
♪ And we'll cook 'em up for dinner ♪

406
00:22:52.371 --> 00:22:53.676
♪ Rollin' up and fryin' up ♪

407
00:22:53.850 --> 00:22:55.678
- Yeah. that's called a fish.
- Woo hoo!

408
00:22:55.852 --> 00:22:59.856
♪ We're gonna go fishin'
next Saturday night ♪

409
00:23:00.030 --> 00:23:01.858
I think my release is
gettin' a lot better.

410
00:23:02.032 --> 00:23:03.556
I've been hangin' around
after practice every day.

411
00:23:03.730 --> 00:23:04.644
workin' on it.

412
00:23:06.036 --> 00:23:07.777
You really love football.
don't you Bradshaw?

413
00:23:07.951 --> 00:23:09.213
Yeah. I do.

414
00:23:09.388 --> 00:23:10.998
More than anything.

415
00:23:11.172 --> 00:23:12.608
Just feels like it's part
of my blood or somethin'.

416
00:23:12.782 --> 00:23:15.045
I feel like that with huntin'.

417
00:23:15.219 --> 00:23:17.134
That's why I ain't playin'
next year [groans].

418
00:23:17.308 --> 00:23:18.179
What?

419
00:23:18.353 --> 00:23:19.876
Are you serious?

420
00:23:20.050 --> 00:23:21.225
NFL scouts have been
watchin' you all year long.

421
00:23:21.400 --> 00:23:22.488
Everybody knows you'll go pro.

422
00:23:22.662 --> 00:23:23.489
Nah.

423
00:23:24.446 --> 00:23:25.316
I'm done.

424
00:23:26.187 --> 00:23:27.057
It's your turn.

425
00:23:28.885 --> 00:23:30.409
You think I'm ready?

426
00:23:30.583 --> 00:23:32.019
Of course you're ready.

427
00:23:32.193 --> 00:23:33.890
No one can throw a bomb
down the field like you.

428
00:23:34.064 --> 00:23:35.979
You're the Blonde Bomber.

429
00:23:36.980 --> 00:23:38.373
The Blonde Bomber?

430
00:23:41.071 --> 00:23:43.944
Guess that's better than
the name you gave Johnson.

431
00:23:44.118 --> 00:23:45.511
What. you mean Old Stubby?

432
00:23:45.685 --> 00:23:47.338
Why you gotta
do him like that. Phil?

433
00:23:47.513 --> 00:23:49.340
It ain't my fault he got
them stubby little legs.

434
00:23:49.515 --> 00:23:51.691
-  Shoot.
- So. I lost my scholarship.

435
00:23:51.865 --> 00:23:54.911
but still managed to finish college.

436
00:23:55.085 --> 00:23:58.437
It was easy enough to
find a job in those days.

437
00:23:58.611 --> 00:24:00.526
The hard part was findin'
one that paid enough.

438
00:24:02.049 --> 00:24:04.312
Our family was growin'.

439
00:24:04.486 --> 00:24:05.574
Hey. boys!

440
00:24:05.748 --> 00:24:06.662
And so were the bills.

441
00:24:06.836 --> 00:24:07.794
Aw. I missed you boys.

442
00:24:07.968 --> 00:24:09.752
Come here. come here.

443
00:24:14.322 --> 00:24:15.192
How you been. huh?

444
00:24:15.366 --> 00:24:17.368
Boy. you gettin' heavy.

445
00:24:17.543 --> 00:24:18.761
Those feet smell?

446
00:24:18.935 --> 00:24:20.502
Boy. they smell bad!

447
00:24:20.676 --> 00:24:21.808
You need to take a shower.

448
00:24:23.331 --> 00:24:25.028
I'm gonna say hi to Mama. okay?

449
00:24:32.296 --> 00:24:36.170
- Hey. baby.
- Hey.

450
00:24:37.432 --> 00:24:38.651
How was your day. hm?

451
00:24:38.825 --> 00:24:41.784
It was good. until Alan tried to stick

452
00:24:41.958 --> 00:24:43.133
a crayon up Jase's nose.

453
00:24:45.179 --> 00:24:45.962
Did it fit?

454
00:24:46.136 --> 00:24:47.529
Hey! Phil [laughs]!

455
00:24:59.759 --> 00:25:00.586
How's it lookin'?

456
00:25:04.154 --> 00:25:05.808
I can feed you out in the woods.

457
00:25:07.288 --> 00:25:08.985
I just need to make
sure we got enough money

458
00:25:09.159 --> 00:25:10.726
to keep a roof over our heads.

459
00:25:16.253 --> 00:25:21.215
I just don't wanna be gone
all the time like my dad was.

460
00:25:21.607 --> 00:25:22.477
You won't.

461
00:25:28.004 --> 00:25:30.964
You got two degrees from Louisiana Tech.

462
00:25:32.835 --> 00:25:34.141
You can do just about anything

463
00:25:34.315 --> 00:25:37.405
you set your mind to. Phil Robertson.

464
00:25:42.802 --> 00:25:43.629
Hey.

465
00:25:45.805 --> 00:25:47.241
I'm proud of you.

466
00:25:48.895 --> 00:25:49.809
I love you.

467
00:25:51.332 --> 00:25:52.725
And I love you.

468
00:25:59.862 --> 00:26:03.692
I wouldn't change anything about us.

469
00:26:03.866 --> 00:26:05.389
We gonna make it.

470
00:26:07.783 --> 00:26:09.785
Stick with me. Miss Kay.

471
00:26:09.959 --> 00:26:13.006
I'll put that long green in your pockets.

472
00:26:17.880 --> 00:26:19.012
Kay was definitely nervous

473
00:26:19.186 --> 00:26:21.580
about me havin' a job interview in a bar.

474
00:26:21.754 --> 00:26:22.711
Was that me?

475
00:26:22.885 --> 00:26:24.278
Was- the bar interview was me?

476
00:26:24.452 --> 00:26:25.322
Yeah.

477
00:26:28.064 --> 00:26:29.109
it was you.

478
00:26:29.283 --> 00:26:30.676
Ah. I had a feelin'.

479
00:26:36.856 --> 00:26:38.727
Yeah. sorry about that.

480
00:26:42.513 --> 00:26:43.558
Good to see ya. Frank.

481
00:26:43.732 --> 00:26:46.605
Oh. oh. oh.

482
00:26:46.779 --> 00:26:48.258
Keep your hands to yourself. Big Al.

483
00:26:48.432 --> 00:26:49.390
You know I can't.

484
00:26:50.696 --> 00:26:53.046
Oh. hey. Sally. why don't you go ahead

485
00:26:53.220 --> 00:26:55.091
and grab me a shot of whiskey?

486
00:26:55.265 --> 00:26:57.616
Hey. you know. make it two.

487
00:26:57.790 --> 00:26:58.660
One for my friend Phil here.

488
00:26:58.834 --> 00:27:00.444
Hey. make it quick.

489
00:27:00.619 --> 00:27:04.535
- You got it.
- He's just catchin' up.

490
00:27:04.710 --> 00:27:06.407
Thank you. Mr. Bolen.

491
00:27:06.581 --> 00:27:07.451
Mr. Bolen?

492
00:27:08.844 --> 00:27:10.498
You must be lookin' for my daddy.

493
00:27:11.455 --> 00:27:12.587
You can call me Big Al.

494
00:27:13.675 --> 00:27:16.547
Okay. sure. Big Al.

495
00:27:17.636 --> 00:27:18.593
Ah.

496
00:27:18.767 --> 00:27:22.641
So. Phil. tell me about yourself.

497
00:27:22.815 --> 00:27:25.165
I got a wife and three
kids I need to support

498
00:27:25.339 --> 00:27:28.037
and teachin' always seemed
like a respectable thing to do.

499
00:27:28.211 --> 00:27:30.257
No. no. no. no [exhales].

500
00:27:30.431 --> 00:27:32.346
I don't mean that shit.

501
00:27:34.348 --> 00:27:35.828
I mean. tell me about you.

502
00:27:36.002 --> 00:27:38.613
What kinda man is Phil Robertson?

503
00:27:39.962 --> 00:27:42.661
Well. I love to hunt.

504
00:27:43.618 --> 00:27:45.359
Now. that's what I'm talkin' 'bout.

505
00:27:45.533 --> 00:27:48.710
Huntin's sure good up
around Junction City.

506
00:27:48.884 --> 00:27:51.104
Keep you real busy on the weekends.

507
00:27:51.278 --> 00:27:53.062
Somethin' to relieve the
stress of the teacher man.

508
00:27:53.236 --> 00:27:54.107
Hm.

509
00:27:58.502 --> 00:27:59.547
Need a smoke?

510
00:27:59.721 --> 00:28:01.549
Oh. I don't really smoke.

511
00:28:05.640 --> 00:28:08.643
Man. you got a sense
of humor. Phil Robertson.

512
00:28:21.003 --> 00:28:22.570
Hell. I knew we were
gonna get along just fine

513
00:28:22.744 --> 00:28:24.441
the moment I shook your hand.

514
00:28:29.577 --> 00:28:30.447
Thank you. Sally.

515
00:28:31.318 --> 00:28:33.450
Hey. and you best keep these comin'.

516
00:28:34.930 --> 00:28:35.801
We got a lot to celebrate tonight.

517
00:28:35.975 --> 00:28:36.802
All right.

518
00:28:38.586 --> 00:28:39.456
That's it?

519
00:28:40.283 --> 00:28:41.415
Did I get the job?

520
00:29:03.698 --> 00:29:06.701
My name is Mr. Robertson.

521
00:29:11.184 --> 00:29:14.187
If y'all could turn your
handbooks to page 45...

522
00:29:21.977 --> 00:29:23.718
Hey. there's my guy.

523
00:29:23.892 --> 00:29:26.286
How 'bout a drink.
celebrate the first day?

524
00:29:27.113 --> 00:29:28.679
I can't.

525
00:29:28.854 --> 00:29:30.899
Miss Kay's got a special
dinner waitin' for me tonight.

526
00:29:31.073 --> 00:29:31.813
Yeah. of course she does.

527
00:29:31.987 --> 00:29:33.249
She's a classy gal.

528
00:29:33.423 --> 00:29:34.555
Well. you ain't a dang derelict.

529
00:29:34.729 --> 00:29:36.600
I'm just talkin' about one drink.

530
00:29:36.775 --> 00:29:38.037
Hey. Fred.

531
00:29:38.211 --> 00:29:39.778
You didn't hear nothin'. Fred.

532
00:29:43.172 --> 00:29:45.479
One drink?

533
00:29:45.653 --> 00:29:46.610
One drink.

534
00:29:47.698 --> 00:29:49.004
Come on. then.

535
00:30:30.393 --> 00:30:31.264
Woo!

536
00:30:32.439 --> 00:30:33.527
- Yes!
- Woo!

537
00:30:47.280 --> 00:30:48.847
- All right.
- Woo!

538
00:30:49.021 --> 00:30:49.978
Line 'em up!

539
00:32:10.058 --> 00:32:13.932
This is as fresh as it
comes. Appaloosa catfish.

540
00:32:14.106 --> 00:32:15.977
That's the filet mignon of the river.

541
00:32:17.239 --> 00:32:19.415
- Jan!
- Hi. Kay.

542
00:32:19.589 --> 00:32:21.287
It's good to see you. sweetheart.

543
00:32:21.461 --> 00:32:22.505
- Hey. Phil.
- Hey. Jan.

544
00:32:22.679 --> 00:32:24.072
How you doin'?

545
00:32:24.246 --> 00:32:24.899
- I'm good. how are you?
- It's good to see you.

546
00:32:25.073 --> 00:32:26.248
You too.

547
00:32:26.422 --> 00:32:27.162
- Hey. hey. how you doin'?
- Hey.

548
00:32:27.336 --> 00:32:28.294
I'm Al.

549
00:32:28.468 --> 00:32:31.079
You must be one of Kay's friends.

550
00:32:31.253 --> 00:32:33.603
I know Phil ain't got
no good lookin' friends.

551
00:32:33.777 --> 00:32:35.301
Well. except for me. of course.

552
00:32:37.042 --> 00:32:37.694
That's my sister.

553
00:32:39.653 --> 00:32:41.307
Okay. okay.

554
00:32:41.481 --> 00:32:42.569
Oh. yeah. okay.

555
00:32:42.743 --> 00:32:43.744
All right.

556
00:32:43.918 --> 00:32:45.789
I mean. I was just bein' friendly.

557
00:32:45.964 --> 00:32:46.877
Why don't you be friendly

558
00:32:47.052 --> 00:32:49.184
in that direction over there. Al?

559
00:32:50.316 --> 00:32:51.143
Okay.

560
00:32:52.405 --> 00:32:54.102
- Sorry about him.
-  No. I'm good.

561
00:32:54.276 --> 00:32:56.191
Hey. congratulations on your new job.

562
00:32:56.365 --> 00:32:57.366
I'm so proud of you.

563
00:32:57.540 --> 00:32:58.846
Thanks. Jan.

564
00:32:59.020 --> 00:33:00.674
Did Kay tell you we took the boys

565
00:33:00.848 --> 00:33:02.110
to church last weekend?

566
00:33:02.284 --> 00:33:03.242
They seemed to really enjoy it.

567
00:33:03.416 --> 00:33:05.026
You should come with us next time.

568
00:33:06.114 --> 00:33:08.421
Yeah. well. I like to spend

569
00:33:08.595 --> 00:33:11.119
my Sunday celebratin' God in other ways.

570
00:33:12.120 --> 00:33:16.124
Who needs a pew when you
can be out in His creation?

571
00:33:16.298 --> 00:33:18.953
Hey. y'all. how 'bout a toast. huh?

572
00:33:20.259 --> 00:33:22.087
To my man Phil Robertson here.

573
00:33:22.261 --> 00:33:26.743
the newest remedial English
teacher at Junction City High.

574
00:33:27.527 --> 00:33:29.050
He ain't smart but he pretty.

575
00:33:31.661 --> 00:33:33.402
I can't do. I can't deal.

576
00:33:33.576 --> 00:33:35.361
- Four ducks?
- Yeah. four ducks.

577
00:33:35.535 --> 00:33:36.579
Four ducks.

578
00:33:36.753 --> 00:33:37.798
One bullet can't take down four ducks.

579
00:33:37.972 --> 00:33:39.234
Oh. it can if you're Phil Robertson.

580
00:33:39.408 --> 00:33:41.106
Who's this new friend with him?

581
00:33:41.280 --> 00:33:42.759
That's Al [throat clears].

582
00:33:44.892 --> 00:33:46.633
He's from his work.

583
00:33:46.807 --> 00:33:48.591
He runs their school.
- Oh. okay.

584
00:33:49.897 --> 00:33:50.854
Yeah. it's that easy.

585
00:33:51.725 --> 00:33:53.031
- Woo ee!
- Woo!

586
00:33:55.946 --> 00:33:56.686
Ow!

587
00:34:03.084 --> 00:34:04.868
Woo!
- Told you boys.

588
00:34:05.043 --> 00:34:07.871
One thing I'm better at
than fishin' is shootin'.

589
00:34:08.742 --> 00:34:09.786
You okay?

590
00:34:09.960 --> 00:34:11.049
- Yeah.
- This here

591
00:34:11.223 --> 00:34:14.356
is some genuine Three Creeks moonshine.

592
00:34:16.315 --> 00:34:17.185
All right.

593
00:34:28.805 --> 00:34:29.676
Daddy?

594
00:34:32.157 --> 00:34:33.245
You goin' huntin'?

595
00:34:34.202 --> 00:34:35.160
You bet ya.

596
00:34:36.944 --> 00:34:37.814
Can I come?

597
00:34:40.121 --> 00:34:41.470
You don't know the woods.

598
00:34:42.428 --> 00:34:44.256
You don't know huntin'.

599
00:34:44.430 --> 00:34:46.736
You could teach me.

600
00:34:54.440 --> 00:34:55.745
Go back to bed.

601
00:35:01.664 --> 00:35:04.624
The next few years were a
bit of a blur. I must admit.

602
00:35:06.843 --> 00:35:09.194
♪ Rumor spreadin' 'round ♪

603
00:35:09.368 --> 00:35:11.848
♪ In that Texas town ♪

604
00:35:12.022 --> 00:35:13.807
You said you know the guy
that owns this property?

605
00:35:13.981 --> 00:35:15.722
Yeah. I met him once.

606
00:35:15.896 --> 00:35:17.115
Well. I met his sister.

607
00:35:17.289 --> 00:35:19.900
♪ And you know what I'm talkin' about ♪

608
00:35:20.074 --> 00:35:21.641
♪ Just let me know ♪
if you wanna go ♪

609
00:35:21.815 --> 00:35:23.860
It was that feeling again.

610
00:35:24.034 --> 00:35:26.167
being pulled in multiple directions.

611
00:35:28.126 --> 00:35:30.476
Huntin'. partying. family.

612
00:35:30.650 --> 00:35:33.696
The drinkin' began to
overtake everything else.

613
00:35:33.870 --> 00:35:37.744
"Airplanes follow duck [indistinct]."

614
00:35:37.918 --> 00:35:39.789
♪ Well. I hear it's fine ♪

615
00:35:41.269 --> 00:35:42.966
I thought it was freedom to my worries.

616
00:35:43.924 --> 00:35:45.839
but it didn't free me from 'em.

617
00:35:46.013 --> 00:35:48.363
It just made me forget about them.

618
00:35:48.537 --> 00:35:49.538
♪ A hmm. hmm ♪

619
00:35:49.712 --> 00:35:52.672
♪ And I hear it's tight ♪

620
00:35:52.846 --> 00:35:54.021
♪ Most every night ♪

621
00:35:56.589 --> 00:35:57.938
♪ But now I might be mistaken ♪

622
00:36:07.034 --> 00:36:09.732
She just will not leave me alone.

623
00:36:11.517 --> 00:36:14.215
I've heard of worse problems than that.

624
00:36:14.389 --> 00:36:15.347
And all I could think was.

625
00:36:15.521 --> 00:36:17.392
"Man. I gotta lay off the sauce."

626
00:36:18.828 --> 00:36:19.829
They respected Phil Robertson.

627
00:36:20.003 --> 00:36:22.528
They know Phil Robertson was a man.

628
00:36:22.702 --> 00:36:23.790
Who's a man?

629
00:36:28.969 --> 00:36:31.101
You're so beautiful. Marleen.

630
00:36:37.325 --> 00:36:39.632
♪ Oh. no ♪

631
00:36:44.289 --> 00:36:47.117
You wasn't
callin' them ducks in. Phil.

632
00:36:47.292 --> 00:36:50.120
You was commandin' them to come in.

633
00:36:50.947 --> 00:36:52.514
Back again?

634
00:36:52.688 --> 00:36:53.863
You don't even have the
decency to hang around here?

635
00:36:54.037 --> 00:36:54.951
I'm cookin' you dinner.

636
00:36:55.125 --> 00:36:56.344
I'm cleanin' up after the kids-

637
00:36:56.518 --> 00:36:58.694
Keep your mouth shut!

638
00:36:58.868 --> 00:37:00.696
What. you can't even have
a conversation with me?

639
00:37:07.312 --> 00:37:08.269
Y'all don't need this.

640
00:37:10.489 --> 00:37:12.317
Class dismissed.

641
00:37:20.934 --> 00:37:22.675
Who's a man?

642
00:37:27.680 --> 00:37:30.248
I was hell-bent
on doin' things my own way.

643
00:37:31.292 --> 00:37:32.250
I always had been.

644
00:37:36.036 --> 00:37:37.385
So. when I had to figure out other ways

645
00:37:37.559 --> 00:37:39.257
to provide for the family.

646
00:37:39.431 --> 00:37:42.172
I went back to the places
that have always provided.

647
00:37:42.347 --> 00:37:44.436
the woods. and the river.

648
00:38:04.760 --> 00:38:06.501
- Take care.
- Oh [speaking faintly].

649
00:38:08.460 --> 00:38:10.636
Miss Abaleen.

650
00:38:12.290 --> 00:38:14.335
Phil Robertson.

651
00:38:14.509 --> 00:38:15.597
You been stayin' outta trouble?

652
00:38:15.771 --> 00:38:16.946
Yes. Ma'am.

653
00:38:17.120 --> 00:38:18.034
How's your mama?

654
00:38:21.299 --> 00:38:22.038
She doin' just great.

655
00:38:22.212 --> 00:38:23.866
Kay and the kids?

656
00:38:24.040 --> 00:38:24.954
It's all good.

657
00:38:25.128 --> 00:38:25.999
Hey?

658
00:38:27.130 --> 00:38:28.741
Got a fresh catch for ya.

659
00:38:28.915 --> 00:38:30.395
You back on the water?

660
00:38:30.569 --> 00:38:31.744
I thought I heard you teachin' down

661
00:38:31.918 --> 00:38:33.528
at that school in Junction City?

662
00:38:33.702 --> 00:38:35.356
Yeah. yeah.

663
00:38:38.272 --> 00:38:40.405
Sabbatical. you know?

664
00:38:41.580 --> 00:38:43.059
Just a short break.

665
00:38:44.583 --> 00:38:46.193
I got myself plenty for the shop today.

666
00:38:46.367 --> 00:38:49.022
You know I don't like
throwin' out no unsold fish.

667
00:38:49.979 --> 00:38:51.720
This here's as fresh as it comes.

668
00:38:51.894 --> 00:38:54.375
You could put this on
special right up front.

669
00:38:57.857 --> 00:38:59.424
Caught no more than an hour ago.

670
00:39:03.515 --> 00:39:04.733
Have a look.

671
00:39:05.778 --> 00:39:06.953
Mm hm.

672
00:39:20.227 --> 00:39:21.010
I appreciate you-

673
00:39:21.184 --> 00:39:22.795
Mm hm.

674
00:39:22.969 --> 00:39:25.188
You best make sure Miss
Kay and the boys get this.

675
00:39:25.363 --> 00:39:26.320
Yes. Ma'am.

676
00:39:26.494 --> 00:39:27.408
Absolutely.

677
00:39:36.548 --> 00:39:37.375
Do.

678
00:39:39.159 --> 00:39:41.335
I'm ashamed to say most of that money

679
00:39:41.509 --> 00:39:44.077
I was makin' didn't go
to Kay and the kids.

680
00:39:44.251 --> 00:39:46.209
but we always found a way to make more.

681
00:39:50.213 --> 00:39:54.043
Hey. if nothin' else. we were creative.

682
00:39:55.436 --> 00:39:58.221
All right. y'all. all bets are in.

683
00:39:58.396 --> 00:40:01.181
Got a rivalry as old as time.

684
00:40:02.530 --> 00:40:05.228
Man versus machine!

685
00:40:05.403 --> 00:40:07.100
Steel versus muscle!

686
00:40:08.754 --> 00:40:11.452
Rubber versus some bare feet.

687
00:40:11.626 --> 00:40:14.368
- Mm hm!
- Yeah. Phil!

688
00:40:14.542 --> 00:40:17.110
- All right.
- Let's go. come on!

689
00:40:17.284 --> 00:40:18.459
Let's get
this show on the boat!

690
00:40:20.592 --> 00:40:21.767
Come on. Phil!

691
00:40:23.682 --> 00:40:26.989
- On your mark.
- You got this. buddy!

692
00:40:29.644 --> 00:40:30.645
get set.

693
00:40:34.170 --> 00:40:35.302
go!

694
00:40:42.657 --> 00:40:44.050
What you doin' there [indistinct]?

695
00:40:44.224 --> 00:40:45.051
Woo!

696
00:40:48.271 --> 00:40:50.186
Just like old times. gentlemen.

697
00:40:51.144 --> 00:40:53.886
Don't give me that sour look
like I'm tryin' to cheat ya.

698
00:40:54.060 --> 00:40:56.192
It's Hank's car and he bet against me.

699
00:40:56.366 --> 00:40:58.194
You think he hamstrung his own bet?

700
00:40:59.108 --> 00:41:01.546
Hey. come on. now. pay up.

701
00:41:01.720 --> 00:41:03.025
Fair and square.

702
00:41:03.939 --> 00:41:06.899
Hey. don't be bitter.

703
00:41:07.073 --> 00:41:08.378
You and I both know Hank's car

704
00:41:08.553 --> 00:41:09.989
ain't got the gun to come even close

705
00:41:10.163 --> 00:41:12.600
to outrunnin' you if you
only give him 20 yards.

706
00:41:13.775 --> 00:41:17.213
You give him 25. he's got you smoked.

707
00:41:19.128 --> 00:41:23.742
Well. that's their fault
for not askin' for 25.

708
00:41:27.180 --> 00:41:28.137
Man. ever since I known you.

709
00:41:28.311 --> 00:41:29.399
you ain't never changed.

710
00:41:29.574 --> 00:41:30.966
Hey. Phil?

711
00:41:31.140 --> 00:41:32.490
Double or nothin'.

712
00:41:34.230 --> 00:41:35.884
Hold my beer.

713
00:41:45.111 --> 00:41:46.460
Hey. Babe.

714
00:41:49.115 --> 00:41:51.552
Guess you decided to finally come home.

715
00:41:52.684 --> 00:41:54.468
I know it's late. I was...

716
00:41:55.556 --> 00:41:57.253
I was. uh.

717
00:41:58.603 --> 00:42:00.387
workin' [sniffs].

718
00:42:01.475 --> 00:42:03.303
Sell some fish?

719
00:42:03.477 --> 00:42:04.696
Yep.

720
00:42:13.356 --> 00:42:14.923
What is this?

721
00:42:16.055 --> 00:42:18.318
That's money I made.

722
00:42:18.492 --> 00:42:20.842
Well. how much fish you sell?

723
00:42:21.016 --> 00:42:22.061
What do you mean?

724
00:42:23.062 --> 00:42:25.064
There's $11 here.

725
00:42:27.545 --> 00:42:31.766
I know. I musta spent
some of it. all right?

726
00:42:34.508 --> 00:42:37.903
Phil. we have three hungry boys.

727
00:42:38.773 --> 00:42:41.559
You put all this pressure on
me to stretch a few dollars.

728
00:42:43.386 --> 00:42:45.911
It is embarrassing havin' a line

729
00:42:46.085 --> 00:42:48.043
of people behind me in
the grocery store waitin'

730
00:42:48.217 --> 00:42:51.090
for me to put stuff back
because I can't afford it.

731
00:42:51.264 --> 00:42:53.179
It's fine.

732
00:42:53.353 --> 00:42:54.876
We're fine.

733
00:42:55.050 --> 00:42:56.704
The kids are fine [chuckles].

734
00:43:00.099 --> 00:43:02.188
I don't think we are. Phil.

735
00:43:06.888 --> 00:43:10.457
Hm. I told you boys. I'm blessed.

736
00:43:10.631 --> 00:43:12.328
I cannot lose.

737
00:43:12.502 --> 00:43:14.374
Jesus don't be playin' no dice.

738
00:43:14.548 --> 00:43:15.636
Only person who can play dice

739
00:43:15.810 --> 00:43:17.595
like that is the devil [laughs].

740
00:43:18.596 --> 00:43:22.425
which will explain why you
riskin' your neck in this bar.

741
00:43:22.600 --> 00:43:23.688
Hm.

742
00:43:24.514 --> 00:43:26.691
Nah. it's 'cause I like the
music and the company better.

743
00:43:26.865 --> 00:43:29.128
- Mm.
- If you went next door.

744
00:43:29.302 --> 00:43:31.217
you'd think they closed the
bar and opened up a morgue.

745
00:43:31.391 --> 00:43:33.915
Really?

746
00:43:34.089 --> 00:43:36.570
Well. I heard that the
owners are lookin' to sell.

747
00:43:37.702 --> 00:43:38.572
Really?

748
00:43:39.878 --> 00:43:42.794
Well. it just so happens
I'm in need of a job.

749
00:43:42.968 --> 00:43:45.753
I said they were sellin'.

750
00:43:45.927 --> 00:43:47.363
not hirin' [chuckles].

751
00:43:49.844 --> 00:43:50.671
They here now?

752
00:44:00.028 --> 00:44:01.247
Jim Perkins?

753
00:44:01.421 --> 00:44:02.291
Yeah.

754
00:44:03.858 --> 00:44:04.903
Phil Robertson.

755
00:44:05.077 --> 00:44:06.731
Nice to meet you.

756
00:44:06.905 --> 00:44:07.819
I heard y'all might be interested

757
00:44:07.993 --> 00:44:09.342
in doin' a little business.

758
00:44:10.735 --> 00:44:12.214
What. you wanna buy the bar?

759
00:44:13.085 --> 00:44:14.303
Well. thought we could talk about

760
00:44:14.477 --> 00:44:16.566
a bit more of a creative strategy.

761
00:44:19.526 --> 00:44:20.396
Hold on.

762
00:44:21.441 --> 00:44:22.747
Hold on.
- Phil!

763
00:44:27.099 --> 00:44:28.013
Keep 'em closed.

764
00:44:30.189 --> 00:44:31.320
Come on.

765
00:44:31.494 --> 00:44:32.757
- Can I open them?
- Not yet.

766
00:44:34.280 --> 00:44:37.457
Just a little further. little further.

767
00:44:40.590 --> 00:44:41.896
Keep 'em closed.

768
00:44:45.073 --> 00:44:46.118
Stand here.

769
00:44:46.292 --> 00:44:48.120
Don't open 'em till I tell ya.

770
00:44:48.294 --> 00:44:49.687
Why does it smell like urine?

771
00:44:54.996 --> 00:44:55.997
Hold on.

772
00:44:58.826 --> 00:44:59.479
Phil?

773
00:45:01.655 --> 00:45:03.309
Okay. open 'em.

774
00:45:09.489 --> 00:45:12.884
It's a bar.

775
00:45:13.058 --> 00:45:15.974
♪ I don't need ♪

776
00:45:16.148 --> 00:45:17.018
You bought a bar?

777
00:45:17.192 --> 00:45:18.585
♪ silver and gold ♪

778
00:45:18.759 --> 00:45:19.717
Sort of.

779
00:45:19.891 --> 00:45:22.894
Phil. we can't afford a bar.

780
00:45:23.068 --> 00:45:24.852
♪ I don't need ♪

781
00:45:25.026 --> 00:45:27.594
I can't even afford groceries.

782
00:45:27.768 --> 00:45:29.030
Don't worry about that.

783
00:45:30.162 --> 00:45:30.989
Look at this.

784
00:45:34.079 --> 00:45:37.082
This is a new start for us as a family.

785
00:45:37.256 --> 00:45:38.213
You been complainin' about money.

786
00:45:38.387 --> 00:45:40.650
we'll make some more money here.

787
00:45:40.825 --> 00:45:43.697
You been complainin' about
not spendin' time together.

788
00:45:43.871 --> 00:45:46.482
well. we'll all be here as a family.

789
00:45:49.094 --> 00:45:50.008
I don't know. Phil.

790
00:45:50.182 --> 00:45:51.009
Hey.

791
00:45:52.227 --> 00:45:53.402
I'll make it up to you.

792
00:45:55.883 --> 00:45:58.668
Kay. I'm gonna make it up to you.

793
00:46:00.583 --> 00:46:03.630
I know things didn't work
out with the teachin' job.

794
00:46:03.804 --> 00:46:05.284
and I was tired.

795
00:46:05.458 --> 00:46:07.808
I wasn't treatin' this family well.

796
00:46:10.637 --> 00:46:14.510
But this is a fresh start for
the Robertson family. okay?

797
00:46:15.729 --> 00:46:17.426
Alan and Jase. they can even help.

798
00:46:23.345 --> 00:46:26.609
Look. I know you're a good man.

799
00:46:26.784 --> 00:46:28.046
I fell in love with that.

800
00:46:32.267 --> 00:46:34.095
But it's the drinkin'.

801
00:46:35.880 --> 00:46:38.317
How's bein' in a bar gonna help with that?

802
00:46:39.535 --> 00:46:42.800
'Cause I'll be workin'. not drinkin'.

803
00:46:43.713 --> 00:46:47.717
Look. you'll keep an eye
on it. I'll keep on it.

804
00:46:50.459 --> 00:46:52.635
I'm gon' make this
work. I want it to work.

805
00:46:56.465 --> 00:46:59.817
You know you're the only one for me.

806
00:46:59.991 --> 00:47:02.645
♪ Darlin' all I need is you ♪

807
00:47:11.524 --> 00:47:12.481
I love you.

808
00:47:18.313 --> 00:47:23.318
I love you.

809
00:47:23.492 --> 00:47:26.104
First thing we gotta do

810
00:47:26.278 --> 00:47:27.714
is get that pee smell outta here though.

811
00:47:27.888 --> 00:47:29.585
'cause that is horrible.

812
00:47:32.153 --> 00:47:33.285
I agree.

813
00:47:33.459 --> 00:47:35.243
I thought I had it figured out [chuckles].

814
00:47:36.505 --> 00:47:38.203
Finally I had arrived.

815
00:47:38.377 --> 00:47:39.944
A way to spend time with my family.

816
00:47:40.118 --> 00:47:42.511
makin' more money. and still get to hang

817
00:47:42.685 --> 00:47:45.297
with my buddies and run
with them all night long.

818
00:47:45.471 --> 00:47:48.213
Daddy. when have I dried enough glasses?

819
00:47:48.387 --> 00:47:49.562
That's the point.

820
00:47:49.736 --> 00:47:51.564
They drink 'em. we clean 'em.

821
00:47:51.738 --> 00:47:54.959
and the whole cycle starts all
over again till closin' time.

822
00:47:55.133 --> 00:47:56.438
You're doin' great. keep goin'.

823
00:47:56.612 --> 00:47:59.267
Hey. get some more peanuts in here.

824
00:48:00.225 --> 00:48:01.139
Okay.

825
00:48:01.313 --> 00:48:02.880
Hey. Phil. get over here.

826
00:48:03.054 --> 00:48:05.534
I got a couple of friends I would like

827
00:48:05.708 --> 00:48:07.362
to introduce you to.

828
00:48:10.626 --> 00:48:14.500
Miss Kay. I'm dyin' here.

829
00:48:14.674 --> 00:48:16.023
Hold on. Billy.

830
00:48:16.197 --> 00:48:17.590
Don't think I don't see you there actin'

831
00:48:17.764 --> 00:48:18.896
like you haven't already
drank the Mississippi

832
00:48:19.070 --> 00:48:20.854
and spent your paycheck tonight.

833
00:48:27.165 --> 00:48:29.254
Why don't you
scoot on over a little bit.

834
00:48:30.951 --> 00:48:32.170
I'm tired of your disrespect!

835
00:48:32.344 --> 00:48:33.823
What is disrespectful about askin' you

836
00:48:33.998 --> 00:48:35.869
to spend one day with your family?

837
00:48:36.043 --> 00:48:37.088
That's all you do!

838
00:48:37.262 --> 00:48:39.917
Nag. nag. nag. nag. nag!

839
00:48:40.091 --> 00:48:41.744
The boys wanna see their daddy!

840
00:48:41.919 --> 00:48:44.182
Oh. don't use your boys to guilt me!

841
00:48:46.662 --> 00:48:49.361
Don't act like I don't
know what you've been up to.

842
00:48:49.535 --> 00:48:51.493
You been out drinkin'
that moonshine again.

843
00:48:51.667 --> 00:48:52.799
I can see it in your eyes.

844
00:48:52.973 --> 00:48:54.670
What the hell does that matter to you?

845
00:48:54.844 --> 00:48:57.064
'Cause it makes you
act like a wild animal.

846
00:48:57.238 --> 00:48:58.413
Oh. you wanna see a wild animal?

847
00:48:58.587 --> 00:48:59.719
Here you go!

848
00:49:29.009 --> 00:49:33.144
Uncle Si!

849
00:49:36.712 --> 00:49:37.539
Come here. boys!

850
00:49:37.713 --> 00:49:40.499
What about it [laughs]?

851
00:49:40.673 --> 00:49:41.804
Oh. man.

852
00:49:42.675 --> 00:49:44.459
Oh. look at you.

853
00:49:44.633 --> 00:49:46.635
Man. y'all growin' faster than
green grass through a goose.

854
00:49:46.809 --> 00:49:47.985
We missed you. Uncle Si.

855
00:49:48.159 --> 00:49:49.421
Oh. buddy. I missed you. too.

856
00:49:49.595 --> 00:49:51.118
I missed you. too.

857
00:49:51.292 --> 00:49:52.250
Where's your mama?

858
00:49:52.424 --> 00:49:53.729
- Inside.
- Miss Kay!

859
00:49:58.038 --> 00:49:59.126
You can't catch me. Jase.

860
00:50:01.128 --> 00:50:03.870
- Get him. Alan!
- Tag. you're it.

861
00:50:07.047 --> 00:50:09.789
- Tag.
- Oh. I got you back.

862
00:50:09.963 --> 00:50:11.312
He becomes the devil. Si.

863
00:50:12.487 --> 00:50:14.489
Mm hm.

864
00:50:14.663 --> 00:50:16.230
I've seen it in his eyes.

865
00:50:19.233 --> 00:50:20.582
But it ain't him.

866
00:50:22.193 --> 00:50:24.891
You know that ain't your brother.

867
00:50:27.024 --> 00:50:29.852
Yeah. well. maybe not.
but I mean. come on.

868
00:50:30.027 --> 00:50:31.289
you don't deserve this.

869
00:50:33.030 --> 00:50:34.901
You're raisin' three boys on your own.

870
00:50:38.731 --> 00:50:41.212
I don't know what I deserve.

871
00:50:44.606 --> 00:50:48.175
Besides. what would
leavin' do to the boys?

872
00:50:49.611 --> 00:50:50.786
They love their daddy.

873
00:50:50.960 --> 00:50:52.484
Go long. Jase!

874
00:50:52.658 --> 00:50:53.528
Okay.

875
00:50:55.574 --> 00:50:58.011
I know it sounds crazy. Si.

876
00:51:00.274 --> 00:51:02.798
but I just know deep in my heart

877
00:51:06.150 --> 00:51:07.673
this family is gon' work out.

878
00:51:19.206 --> 00:51:20.077
Well.

879
00:51:22.122 --> 00:51:23.167
you know he ain't gonna change.

880
00:51:23.341 --> 00:51:24.820
not unless he stops drinkin'.

881
00:51:26.953 --> 00:51:27.823
I know.

882
00:51:32.654 --> 00:51:37.268
But you know. my Nanny
told me that someday

883
00:51:38.530 --> 00:51:40.749
you gonna have to fight for your marriage.

884
00:51:44.144 --> 00:51:47.234
When things get tough. that's what you do.

885
00:51:51.412 --> 00:51:52.152
You fight.

886
00:52:02.510 --> 00:52:05.687
Excuse me. ladies. gimme one second.

887
00:52:09.735 --> 00:52:10.562
Hey. Phil?

888
00:52:14.392 --> 00:52:15.828
There's someone here to see you.

889
00:52:26.230 --> 00:52:27.622
Who's responsible for this?

890
00:52:27.796 --> 00:52:30.103
Do you know where you'd
go if you die tonight?

891
00:52:31.104 --> 00:52:31.800
Jan?

892
00:52:33.150 --> 00:52:34.716
Hi. Phil.

893
00:52:34.890 --> 00:52:36.675
What you doin' here. Jan?

894
00:52:36.849 --> 00:52:38.981
Well. you ain't returned
my calls in forever.

895
00:52:39.156 --> 00:52:40.766
so I thought I'd check in on you.

896
00:52:42.115 --> 00:52:43.682
This your new boyfriend?

897
00:52:43.856 --> 00:52:47.425
Phil Robertson. this
is Pastor Bill Smith.

898
00:52:48.382 --> 00:52:51.124
How you doin' there. Phil?

899
00:52:51.298 --> 00:52:53.779
What ya sellin' preacher man?

900
00:52:53.953 --> 00:52:58.349
Naw. we ain't sellin'
nothin'. just offerin'.

901
00:52:59.393 --> 00:53:01.395
Just God and the good news.

902
00:53:03.919 --> 00:53:05.747
Don't you read "Times Magazine?"

903
00:53:06.879 --> 00:53:07.923
God is dead.

904
00:53:10.535 --> 00:53:12.450
Yeah. that's not been my experience.

905
00:53:13.755 --> 00:53:17.324
But I have been in here less than maybe

906
00:53:17.498 --> 00:53:20.936
a minute or two and I can already see

907
00:53:21.110 --> 00:53:23.417
you got one mighty chip on your shoulder.

908
00:53:30.076 --> 00:53:31.860
I should knock you out right here.

909
00:53:32.905 --> 00:53:34.167
You can try.

910
00:53:34.341 --> 00:53:35.212
Oh.

911
00:53:37.126 --> 00:53:38.345
Tall words from a preacher man

912
00:53:38.519 --> 00:53:41.043
who can't do nothin' about it.

913
00:53:42.306 --> 00:53:44.046
Jesus says I got to forgive you.

914
00:53:46.788 --> 00:53:50.357
but that don't mean he
won't forgive me. too.

915
00:53:50.531 --> 00:53:51.358
Phil.

916
00:53:53.186 --> 00:53:56.320
Jan. why you bringin' a
preacher man around here?

917
00:53:58.235 --> 00:54:01.412
Well. I heard you might be needin' one.

918
00:54:04.153 --> 00:54:05.981
Preachers ain't welcome 'round here.

919
00:54:07.940 --> 00:54:08.897
Let's go. Jan.

920
00:54:10.682 --> 00:54:12.161
He ain't ready yet.

921
00:54:12.336 --> 00:54:13.467
How you doin'. Ma'am?

922
00:54:13.641 --> 00:54:14.599
Excuse me.
- Jan. you should stay.

923
00:54:14.773 --> 00:54:16.165
Have a drink.

924
00:54:16.340 --> 00:54:17.906
I'm gonna be prayin' for you.

925
00:54:20.779 --> 00:54:22.563
Then you'll be wastin' your time.

926
00:54:24.130 --> 00:54:26.175
All right then.

927
00:54:26.350 --> 00:54:28.047
All right. God bless yourself.

928
00:54:35.837 --> 00:54:36.925
You put her up to it.

929
00:54:37.099 --> 00:54:38.579
I didn't.

930
00:54:38.753 --> 00:54:40.277
I swear. I didn't know
she was comin' around.

931
00:54:40.451 --> 00:54:41.930
Don't lie to me.

932
00:54:42.104 --> 00:54:43.932
I saw the way she was lookin' at you.

933
00:54:46.674 --> 00:54:48.807
This is just you tryin' to control me.

934
00:54:48.981 --> 00:54:49.721
All of you.

935
00:54:49.895 --> 00:54:52.289
Phil. please. please.

936
00:54:52.463 --> 00:54:54.900
I swear to God. you better
hold that tongue of yours.

937
00:54:55.074 --> 00:54:56.771
Phil. you're hurtin' my arm.

938
00:54:56.945 --> 00:54:58.773
If I found out you been tellin'
people about our business-

939
00:54:58.947 --> 00:55:00.732
Phil. you're hurtin' me.

940
00:55:18.402 --> 00:55:19.794
What'll it be. boys?

941
00:55:19.968 --> 00:55:21.361
Hm?

942
00:55:21.535 --> 00:55:23.668
Hey. sweetheart. that
pie recipe she gave me.

943
00:55:23.842 --> 00:55:25.626
my boys. they go crazy for it [chuckles].

944
00:55:25.800 --> 00:55:26.801
They do [chuckles].

945
00:55:28.107 --> 00:55:29.064
Where you been?

946
00:55:29.238 --> 00:55:31.023
Pretty late for grocery shoppin'.

947
00:55:31.197 --> 00:55:33.155
Well. when am I supposed to go?

948
00:55:33.330 --> 00:55:34.983
Been at the bar all day. Phil.

949
00:55:35.157 --> 00:55:36.811
You were with him. weren't ya?

950
00:55:36.985 --> 00:55:38.900
What are you talkin' about?

951
00:55:39.074 --> 00:55:39.814
That guy from the bar.

952
00:55:43.252 --> 00:55:44.515
Phil. I'm tired.

953
00:55:44.689 --> 00:55:46.865
It's been a long day and you been drinkin'

954
00:55:47.039 --> 00:55:48.867
through most of it.

955
00:55:49.041 --> 00:55:51.870
My drinkin' ain't got
nothin' to do with it.

956
00:55:52.044 --> 00:55:54.481
How long you been
runnin' 'round on me. hm?

957
00:55:54.655 --> 00:55:56.831
Answer the damn question.

958
00:55:58.050 --> 00:56:00.400
I ain't runnin' around on you.

959
00:56:01.358 --> 00:56:02.794
I know you're lyin'.

960
00:56:04.578 --> 00:56:06.711
Phil. I ain't havin'
this conversation now.

961
00:56:06.885 --> 00:56:08.103
Not when you're drunk.

962
00:56:08.277 --> 00:56:09.366
I ain't the problem.

963
00:56:10.323 --> 00:56:11.542
You're the problem.

964
00:56:11.716 --> 00:56:13.326
You're ruinin' my life!

965
00:56:13.500 --> 00:56:14.936
Oh. yeah?

966
00:56:15.110 --> 00:56:18.287
Well. you been ruinin' mine for 10 years!

967
00:56:21.595 --> 00:56:22.422
Get out.

968
00:56:24.729 --> 00:56:26.513
Get out and take your kids with you.

969
00:57:02.854 --> 00:57:03.985
Good Lord. Phil.

970
00:57:06.248 --> 00:57:07.685
I can't hardly believe that.

971
00:57:12.864 --> 00:57:16.084
I can't believe the thought
of what I did most days.

972
00:57:20.785 --> 00:57:23.004
But that was a point
where I'd lost it all.

973
00:57:25.703 --> 00:57:26.530
Kay.

974
00:57:29.097 --> 00:57:29.924
the boys.

975
00:57:31.578 --> 00:57:32.449
the bar.

976
00:57:34.276 --> 00:57:35.147
Bingo.

977
00:57:36.801 --> 00:57:38.063
Just like that.

978
00:58:07.788 --> 00:58:09.703
Kay. what's happenin'?

979
00:58:09.877 --> 00:58:11.052
What's goin' on? Come in.

980
00:58:11.226 --> 00:58:12.401
Come on in.

981
00:58:28.809 --> 00:58:29.636
Thanks.

982
00:58:34.859 --> 00:58:36.600
You can stay as long as you want.

983
00:58:40.125 --> 00:58:41.996
I can't trouble you like that.

984
00:58:42.170 --> 00:58:44.869
Trust me. it's no trouble at all.

985
00:58:46.914 --> 00:58:49.047
You're not worried
about Phil findin' out?

986
00:58:51.310 --> 00:58:52.398
He kicked you out.

987
00:58:58.186 --> 00:59:00.667
Why don't you go freshen up?

988
00:59:00.841 --> 00:59:02.016
I'll listen for Willie.

989
00:59:10.242 --> 00:59:11.112
Thank you. Jan.

990
00:59:12.200 --> 00:59:13.201
Of course.

991
01:01:09.578 --> 01:01:11.363
Are you okay. Mama?

992
01:01:14.540 --> 01:01:15.933
Mama?

993
01:01:16.107 --> 01:01:16.934
Hey.

994
01:01:18.283 --> 01:01:19.588
What's goin' on?

995
01:01:19.763 --> 01:01:21.199
It's Mama.

996
01:01:24.942 --> 01:01:27.640
Okay. okay. just go
back to bed. all right?

997
01:01:27.814 --> 01:01:28.467
Back to bed.

998
01:01:28.641 --> 01:01:29.511
I'll check.

999
01:01:34.212 --> 01:01:35.474
Kay?

1000
01:01:41.610 --> 01:01:45.310
Kay. are you all right?

1001
01:02:22.739 --> 01:02:26.481
I was thinkin' about
somethin' real stupid.

1002
01:02:34.794 --> 01:02:36.578
I was about to do it.

1003
01:02:39.712 --> 01:02:44.717
I just kept thinkin' about
those boys [sobs softly].

1004
01:02:50.462 --> 01:02:51.724
I'm their mama.

1005
01:02:53.944 --> 01:02:56.990
I can't just leave 'em alone.

1006
01:02:57.164 --> 01:02:58.513
No. you can't.

1007
01:03:05.259 --> 01:03:09.481
I really believed it was
gon' work out with Phil.

1008
01:03:11.439 --> 01:03:12.527
I really did.

1009
01:03:18.098 --> 01:03:22.189
But it's over [inhales shakily].

1010
01:03:25.192 --> 01:03:27.629
I just don't know what to do.

1011
01:03:34.375 --> 01:03:35.246
Well.

1012
01:03:39.903 --> 01:03:42.775
you can start by gettin'
up off the bathroom floor.

1013
01:03:49.216 --> 01:03:54.178
When I was little. and
Mama was in the hospital.

1014
01:03:56.310 --> 01:03:58.008
and Daddy was on the oil rigs.

1015
01:04:00.837 --> 01:04:03.056
I used to cry myself to sleep every night.

1016
01:04:06.146 --> 01:04:06.973
And then

1017
01:04:08.627 --> 01:04:10.585
one Sunday.

1018
01:04:10.759 --> 01:04:14.981
I heard the preacher down at church sayin'

1019
01:04:15.155 --> 01:04:16.983
that at some point in our lives.

1020
01:04:18.593 --> 01:04:23.381
we are all going to
feel desperately alone.

1021
01:04:25.862 --> 01:04:30.823
like we're the only soul
in the whole entire world.

1022
01:04:30.997 --> 01:04:34.653
and that that would be
the most important moment

1023
01:04:34.827 --> 01:04:36.481
in our whole entire lives

1024
01:04:38.091 --> 01:04:42.530
because when we realize that with Jesus.

1025
01:04:44.315 --> 01:04:46.056
we ain't never alone.

1026
01:04:49.233 --> 01:04:50.060
So.

1027
01:04:52.366 --> 01:04:55.021
I stopped cryin' myself to sleep at night.

1028
01:04:56.893 --> 01:04:59.373
and I started prayin' instead.

1029
01:05:02.159 --> 01:05:04.596
I'll watch the boys tomorrow.

1030
01:05:05.989 --> 01:05:07.729
There's someone you gotta go see.

1031
01:05:23.397 --> 01:05:25.269
Hey. that was a good one.

1032
01:05:25.443 --> 01:05:26.531
I appreciate ya.

1033
01:05:26.705 --> 01:05:29.751
God bless ya. I'll see ya on Wednesday.

1034
01:05:39.326 --> 01:05:40.632
Pastor Smith?

1035
01:05:40.806 --> 01:05:42.155
Yeah?

1036
01:05:42.329 --> 01:05:43.156
Hi.

1037
01:05:44.070 --> 01:05:44.984
I'm Kay Robertson.

1038
01:05:46.464 --> 01:05:47.856
Right.

1039
01:05:48.031 --> 01:05:49.771
Jan told me you might stop by.

1040
01:05:49.946 --> 01:05:51.382
It's good to see you again. Miss Kay.

1041
01:05:51.556 --> 01:05:52.600
It's been a bit.

1042
01:05:53.558 --> 01:05:56.865
I'm really sorry about my husband.

1043
01:05:58.867 --> 01:06:01.870
The first time at the bar-

1044
01:06:02.045 --> 01:06:03.002
Would it surprise you if I told you

1045
01:06:03.176 --> 01:06:04.699
I get that reaction a lot?

1046
01:06:07.441 --> 01:06:08.268
I guess not.

1047
01:06:09.443 --> 01:06:10.488
How's your husband?

1048
01:06:17.103 --> 01:06:19.105
He kicked us outta the house yesterday.

1049
01:06:20.759 --> 01:06:21.890
Me and my three boys.

1050
01:06:26.112 --> 01:06:27.505
Sorry to hear that.

1051
01:06:30.638 --> 01:06:32.597
Look. Jan said to come talk to you.

1052
01:06:34.599 --> 01:06:36.557
maybe you might be able to help us out.

1053
01:06:38.429 --> 01:06:42.389
But I don't really know
what I'm doin' here.

1054
01:06:43.825 --> 01:06:46.045
or what even to say and...

1055
01:06:52.834 --> 01:06:57.361
I guess I got into some
trouble last night.

1056
01:06:59.493 --> 01:07:00.538
thinkin' about some things

1057
01:07:00.712 --> 01:07:02.322
I shouldn't have been thinkin' about.

1058
01:07:04.933 --> 01:07:05.804
And...

1059
01:07:07.284 --> 01:07:08.676
I'm really sorry.

1060
01:07:08.850 --> 01:07:10.504
You must be so busy.

1061
01:07:10.678 --> 01:07:11.897
It's not a problem.

1062
01:07:13.942 --> 01:07:14.813
Truly.

1063
01:07:18.338 --> 01:07:19.513
You know. Miss Kay. it's the strangest

1064
01:07:19.687 --> 01:07:20.732
thing you should come by.

1065
01:07:20.906 --> 01:07:23.735
